'''''Knightmare''''' is a video  game released by [[Activision]] in 1987 for [[ZX Spectrum]], [[Amstrad CPC]], [[Commodore 64]], and [[Atari ST]]. It was written by [[Mev Dinc]], J.P. Dean, E.M. Dean and Nick Cooke, and is based on the [[ITV Anglia|Anglia Television]] show ''[[Knightmare (TV series)|Knightmare]]''. Four years later, [[Mindscape (company)|Mindscape]] released entirely different game based on the show, also called ''[[Knightmare (1991 video game)|Knightmare]]'', for the Atari ST and [[Amiga]].

==Gameplay==
The player is trapped in a [[dungeon]] and must attempt to escape by solving various [[puzzle]]s. Casting [[Spell (paranormal)|spells]] is also a part of the gameplay. There are six spells: Anvil, Casper, Alchemy, Ice, Toad and Metamorph. Each has a unique result. The game is controlled by using both the [[joystick]] and [[Computer keyboard|keyboard]]. Foes include [[spider]]s and [[monster]]s.<ref name="Zzap64">{{cite magazine| title=Knightmare C64 Review | magazine=Zzap!64 | publisher=Europress | date=February 1988}}</ref>

