''[[Zzap!64]]'' reviewed the Commodore 64 version of the game and said ''Knightmare'' is a pretty tough game, but is worth playing if you are an adventure game fan. It noted that the audio in the game is poor, with no [[Video game music|music]] and only [[sound effect]]s. The magazine rated the game 66 percent.<ref name="Zzap64" /> [[Sinclair User]] magazine rated the game highly, drawing attention to the interesting [[subplot]]s and the originality of the [[gameplay]].<ref>{{cite magazine | title=Knightmare Sinclair Spectrum review | magazine=Sinclair User | publisher=EMAP | date=February 1987}}</ref> ''[[Computer and Video Games]]'' magazine said that the gameplay in ''Knightmare'' is much simpler than the concept used in the television show. The magazine praised the puzzles and style, calling ''Knightmare'' a thoroughly enjoyable game.<ref>{{citation | title=Computer + Video Games review | author=Boughton, Paul | publisher=EMAP | date=February 1988}}</ref>

